description:
God’s prophet Jeremiah was called to prophesy against the sins of Judah just before the destruction of Jerusalem by Nebuchadnezzar. The events in his time serve as a type for the events at the end of time in God’s church. We are admonished in the Spirit of Prophecy to study the book of Jeremiah because it not only serves as a type of the condition of the children of Israel, but also is a type of the Three Angels’ Messages. 

In this typological study of the book of Jeremiah, the weeping prophet, Walter Veith applies important lessons to God’s church. Let the sword of the Word as wielded by Prophet Jeremiah cut to your heart in this typological study.
